<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;2.4 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">2.4
&#147;Business Day&#148; shall mean any day except Saturday, Sunday, or a statutory
or banking holiday observed in the jurisdiction specified pursuant to Section
14.5. A Business Day shall open at 8:00 a.m. and close at 5:00 p.m. local time
for the relevant party&#146;s principal place of business. The relevant party, in
each instance unless otherwise specified, shall be the party to whom the Notice
is being sent and by whom the Notice is to be received.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;2.8 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">2.8 &#147;Contract Price&#148; shall mean, if the Delivery Point is in the United States,
the amount expressed in U.S. Dollars per MMBtu or, if the Delivery Point is in
Canada, the amount expressed in Canadian Dollars per GJ, unless specified
otherwise in a transaction, to be paid by Buyer to Seller for the purchase of
Gas as agreed to by the parties in a transaction.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following as Section&nbsp;2.30:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">2.30 &#147;GJ&#148; shall mean 1 gigajoule; 1 gigajoule = 1,000,000,000 Joules. The
standard conversion factor between Dekatherms and GJ&#146;s is 1.055056 GJ&#146;s per
Dekatherm.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following as Section&nbsp;2.31:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">2.31 &#147;Joule&#148; shall mean the joule specified in the SI system of units.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following as Section&nbsp;2.32:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">2.32 &#147;Termination Currency Equivalent&#148; shall mean, in respect of any amount
denominated in a currency other than the Termination Currency (the &#147;Other
Currency&#148;), the amount in the Termination Currency that the Non-Defaulting
Party would be required to pay, on the Early Termination Date, to purchase such
amount of Other Currency for spot delivery, as determined by the Non-Defaulting
Party in a commercially reasonable manner.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;5 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">All Gas delivered by Seller shall meet the pressure, quality and heat content
requirements of the Receiving Transporter. The unit of quantity measurement
for purposes of this Contract shall be one MMBtu dry or one GJ, as agreed to by
the parties in a transaction. Measurement of Gas quantities hereunder shall be
in accordance with the established procedures of the Receiving Transporter.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following to Section&nbsp;6:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Sections&nbsp;6.2, 6.3 and 6.4 apply if the Delivery Point is in Canada.</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.2 The Contract Price does not include any amounts payable by Buyer for the goods and services tax (&#147;GST&#148;) imposed pursuant
to the Excise Tax Act (Canada) (&#147;ETA&#148;) or any similar or replacement value added or sales or use tax enacted under successor
legislation. Notwithstanding whether the parties have selected &#147;Buyer Pays At and After Delivery Point&#148; or &#147;Seller Pays Before
and At Delivery Point&#148; as indicated on the Base Contract, Buyer will pay to Seller the amount of GST payable for the purchase
of Gas in addition to all other amounts payable under the Contract. Seller will hold the GST paid by Buyer and will remit such
GST as required by law. Buyer and Seller will provide each other with the information required to make such GST remittance or
claim any corresponding input tax credits, including GST registration numbers.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.3 Where Buyer indicates to Seller that Gas will be exported from Canada, the following shall apply:


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.3.1 Where Buyer is not registered for GST under the ETA and Buyer indicates to Seller that Gas will be exported from Canada,
Buyer may request Seller treat such Gas as &#147;zero-rated&#148; Gas for export within the meaning of the ETA for billing purposes. If
Seller, in its sole discretion, agrees to so treat such Gas, then Buyer hereby declares, represents and warrants to Seller
that Buyer will: (i)&nbsp;export such Gas as soon as is reasonably possible after Seller delivers such Gas to Buyer (or after such
Gas is delivered to Buyer after a zero-rated storage service under the ETA) having regard to the circumstances surrounding the
export and, where applicable, normal business practice; (ii)&nbsp;not acquire such Gas for consumption or use in Canada (other than
as fuel or compressor gas to transport such Gas by pipeline) or for supply in Canada (other than to supply natural gas liquids
or ethane the consideration for which is deemed by the ETA to be nil) before export of such Gas; (iii)&nbsp;ensure that, after such
Gas is delivered and before export, such Gas is not further processed, transformed or altered in Canada (except to the extent
reasonably necessary or incidental to its transportation and other than to recover natural gas liquids or ethane from such Gas
at a straddle plant); (iv)&nbsp;maintain on file, and provide to Seller, if required, or to the Canada Customs and Revenue Agency,
evidence satisfactory to the Minister of National Revenue of the export of such Gas by Buyer; and/or (v)&nbsp;comply with all other
requirements prescribed by the ETA for a zero-rated export of such Gas.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.3.2 Where Buyer is registered for GST under the ETA and Buyer indicates to Seller that Gas will be exported from Canada,
Buyer may request Seller treat such Gas as &#147;zero-rated&#148; Gas for export within the meaning of the ETA for billing purposes, and
Buyer hereby declares, represents and warrants to Seller that Buyer intends to export such Gas by means of pipeline or other
conduit in circumstances described in Section&nbsp;6.3.1 (i)&nbsp;to (iii).


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.3.3 Without limiting the generality of Section&nbsp;8.3, Buyer indemnifies Seller for any GST, penalties and interest and all
other

<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.4 In the event that any amount becomes payable pursuant to the Contract as a result of a breach, modification or termination

<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;7.5 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">7.5 If the invoiced party fails to remit the full amount payable when due,
interest on the unpaid portion shall accrue from the date due until the date of

States currency, the then-effective prime rate of interest published under
&#147;Money Rates&#148; by The Wall Street Journal, plus two percent per annum; or, if

<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;7.7 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">7.7 Unless the parties have elected on the Base Contract not to make this
Section&nbsp;7.7 applicable to this Contract, the parties shall net
all undisputed amounts due and owing, and/or past due, in the same currency,
arising under the Contract such that the party owing the greater amount shall
make a single payment of the net amount to the other party in accordance with
Section&nbsp;7; provided that no payment required to be made pursuant to the terms
of any Credit Support Obligation or pursuant to Section&nbsp;7.3 shall be subject to
netting under this Section. If the parties have executed a separate netting
agreement, the terms and conditions therein shall prevail to the extent
inconsistent herewith.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following as Section&nbsp;7.8:</B>

of the Contract Price for such transaction.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Add the following as Section&nbsp;10.3.4:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">10.3.4 The Non-Defaulting Party shall use the Termination Currency Equivalent
of any amount denominated in a currency other than the Termination Currency in
performing any netting, aggregation or setoff required or permitted by Section
10.3.1 or 10.3.2.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;10.4 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">10.4. As soon as practicable after a liquidation, Notice shall be given by the
Non-Defaulting Party to the Defaulting Party of the Net Settlement Amount, and
whether the Net Settlement Amount is due to or due from the Non-Defaulting
Party. The Notice shall include a written statement explaining in reasonable
detail the calculation of such amount, provided that failure to give such
Notice shall not affect the validity or enforceability of the liquidation or
give rise to any claim by the Defaulting Party against the Non-Defaulting
Party. The Net Settlement Amount shall be paid, in the Termination Currency, by
the close of business on the second Business Day following such Notice, which
date shall not be earlier than the Early Termination Date. Interest on any
unpaid portion of the Net Settlement Amount shall accrue from the date due
until the date of payment at a rate equal to the lower of: (i)&nbsp;if the amount
payable is in United States currency, the then-effective prime rate of interest
published under &#147;Money Rates&#148; by The Wall Street Journal, plus two percent per
annum; or, if the amount payable is in Canadian currency, the per annum rate of
interest identified from time to time as the prime lending rate charged to its
most credit worthy customers for Canadian currency commercial loans by The
Toronto Dominion Bank, Main Branch, Calgary, Alberta, Canada, plus two percent
per annum; or (ii)&nbsp;the maximum applicable lawful interest rate.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt"><B>Delete Section&nbsp;10.5 and replace it with the following:</B>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">10.5 The parties agree that the transactions hereunder constitute a &#147;forward
contract&#148; within the meaning of the United States Bankruptcy Code and that
Buyer and Seller are each &#147;forward contract merchants&#148; within the meaning of
the United States Bankruptcy Code. The parties also agree that the transactions
hereunder constitute an &#147;eligible financial contract&#148; within the meaning of the

Act (Canada), and similar Canadian legislation.

<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Contract Price:


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Monthly Contract Price = &#091; (0.90 * AMI &#043; 1.0 * NDC) * CR * ER &#093;, where AMI, NDC, CR and ER are defined as follows:


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">AMI (Alberta Monthly Indext) = the &#147;AECO &#147;C&#148; &#038; N.I.T. One Month Spot as reported for the applicable month in the Canadian Gas Price Reporter ,&#147;Avg&#148;
column in units of $CA/GJ.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">NDC (NOVA Delivery Charge)= the Nova Delivery Charges at Empress for the applicable month, equal to the sum of, as applicable, the delivery demand
charges, the delivery variable commodity charges, and the delivery fuel charges, subject to a cap of 0.30 US$/mmBTU.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">CR (Conversion Rate) = 1.055056 GJ/MMBtu


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">ER (US$/CA$ Exchange Rate) = the &#147;Canada/U.S. Exchange Rate&#148; for the applicable month as reported in the Canadian Gas Price Reporter




<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Delivery Period: Begin: November 1 , 2009&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; End: October&nbsp;31, 2014

    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top"><U>20,660</U> MMBtus/day Maximum</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="bottom">
    <TD valign="top"><DIV style="margin-left:0px; text-indent:-0px">
</DIV></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top">subject to Section&nbsp;4.2. at election of</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="bottom">
    <TD valign="top"><DIV style="margin-left:0px; text-indent:-0px">
</DIV></TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top">x Buyer or <FONT face="Wingdings">&#111;</FONT> Seller</TD>
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD align="left" valign="top">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<!-- End Table Body -->
</TABLE>
</DIV>





<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt"><B>Delivery Point(s): </B>Empress, into TCPL mainline



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">(If a pooling point is used, list a specific geographic and pipeline location)

Ratin</B>g (Section&nbsp;6.3): &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#091;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#093; No (default) &#091;x&#093; Yes

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt"><B>Attachment 1- Special Conditions</B>



<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(i)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Conditions Precedent: This Transaction Confirmation is subject to
the condition precedent of the execution of an amending agreement
concerning the pricing for all volumes delivered under the Gas Sale and
Purchase Contract between Buyer and Seller dated October&nbsp;22, 1992, as
amended (&#147;Existing Agreement&#148;).</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(ii)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Prior Period Agreement: To the extent that any National Energy Board
approval requirements, under the current long term export license, for
the amending agreement referred to in (i)&nbsp;above delays the effective
date such amending agreement past November&nbsp;1, 2004, then Buyer agrees
to keep Seller financially whole as if the amending agreement took
effect November&nbsp;1, 2004 by paying Seller the positive difference (zero
if negative) between the contract price under the Existing Agreement
and the contract price under the amending agreement for all volumes
delivered under the Existing Agreement.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(iii)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Annual Minimum Take Obligation of Buyer: The Buyer&#146;s obligation to
take under this Transaction Confirmation is subject to a minimum annual
take obligation during each Contract Year, as defined below, of 69% of
the maximum daily quantity times 365&nbsp;days, provided that Buyer provides
Seller with 2 Business Days notice whenever volume to be taken on any
day is less than the maximum contract quantity of 20,660 MMBTu/d.
&#147;Contract Year&#148; means November 1 through October&nbsp;31.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(iv)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Liquidated Damages: Seller agrees to pay liquidated damages under
section 3.2 if Buyer is unable to export gas from Canada due to
suspension, if applicable, of Seller&#146;s short or long term removal permit
by the Alberta Energy Resources Conservation Board or Buyer&#146;s short or
long term export permit by the National Energy Board.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(v)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Replacement Oil Index: Buyer agrees to apply a replacement No.&nbsp;2 fuel
oil index for October&nbsp;2004 deliveries defined as follows: &#147;the US
Wholesale Posted Price for PAD1, MetroNY (Eth) Diesel No.2 Fuel&#148;.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(vi)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Settlement of Outstanding Accounts and Release and Discharge: Buyer
will pay Seller $US 500,000 to settle all outstanding billing and/or
other contractual issues under or relating to the Existing Agreement
(whether known or unknown, liquidated or unliquidated, actual or
contingent (&#147;Disputes&#148;). Buyer and Seller agree that such payment
resolves all Disputes, that the other party has satisfied its payment,
supply and all other obligations related to the Existing Agreement
outstanding as of October&nbsp;31, 2004 and for the period November&nbsp;1, 1994
through December&nbsp;31, 2004 and each party releases and forever discharges
the other from any and all further payment, obligation, debt or
liability whatsoever with respect to the Disputes through December&nbsp;31,
2004. Seller agrees to receive payment for these adjustments in
accordance with the following schedule: 100,000 US$ in December, 2004
and then 80,000 US$ in each month over period January&nbsp;2005 to May&nbsp;2005.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(vii)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>No Restriction on Gas Use: Seller acknowledges that there is no
restriction on Buyer&#146;s use or utilization of Contract Quantities under
this Agreement.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(viii)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Termination by Buyer: Should Seller be unable to secure the extension
of its existing Alberta Energy and Utilities Board (&#147;AEUB&#148;) removal
permit or obtain a new AEUB removal permits to allow deliveries of Gas
hereunder through October&nbsp;31, 2014, Buyer may, at its sole option, waive
its right to liquidated damages as described in Section&nbsp;IV of these
Special Conditions and instead terminate this transaction.
Additionally, should Buyer no longer be a party to the power purchase
agreement defined in Section&nbsp;1.1(h) of the Existing Agreement, Buyer
may, at its sole option, terminate this transaction upon 90&nbsp;days advance
written notice to Seller. In the case of any termination by Buyer under
this Section&nbsp;X, neither party shall have any liability to the other for
the payment of any amounts pursuant to Section&nbsp;10.3 of this Contract.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">(ix)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>For this transaction only, Section&nbsp;14.6 is amended by adding at the end of the Section, the following:</TD>
</TR>

    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;Contract Price does not include any sales, use, gross receipt,

    <TD>&#147;2.26 &#147;Spot Price&#148; as referred to in Section&nbsp;3.2 shall mean AMI plus NDC,
where AMI and NDC are defined as follows: AMI = the &#147;AECO &#147;C&#148; &#038; N.I.T.
One Month Spot as reported in the Canadian Gas Price Reporter ,&#147;Avg&#148;
column in units of $/GJ and NDC = Nova delivery charges at Empress,
including, as applicable, demand charges, variable commodity charges and
fuel charges, subject to a cap of 0.30 US$/mmBTU.&#148;</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>


<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">

<TR>

    <TD>&#147;Seller shall have the right, but not the obligation, to deliver all, or any

Confirmation, from alternate sources of production at no additional cost to
Buyer. Such Gas shall be delivered to Buyer at the Delivery Point(s) or at
&#147;Alternate Delivery Point(s)&#148;, where said term shall mean any mutually
agreeable point(s) of delivery, other than the Delivery Point(s) set forth

    <TD>&#147;3.5. Seller, at no additional cost to Buyer, reserves the right to process

the Delivery Point(s) and retain title to the gas liquids. In the event such
processing occurs downstream of the Delivery Point(s), the volume measured
at the Delivery Point(s) shall be increased to adjust for processing plant
fuel and shrinkage. Seller shall bear all the costs of transportation
attributable to plant fuel and shrinkage.&#148;</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">3.</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD><B>Section&nbsp;4. Transportation, Nominations, and Imbalances</B></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right"></TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(a) Add the following sentence to the end of Section&nbsp;4.3:</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;Under no circumstances shall a party be responsible for Imbalance Charges
related to excess or unauthorized takes, violations of Operational Flow
Orders, or similar penalties, related to the other party&#146;s receipt or
delivery of quantities of Gas greater than or less than the Scheduled Gas,
as such Scheduled Gas may be adjusted from time to time.&#148;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">4.</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD><B>Section&nbsp;7. Billing, Payment, and Audit</B></TD>

    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(a) Insert the following at the end of the second sentence of Section&nbsp;7.6:</TD>

    <TD>&#147;and to the extent that any proprietary information is made available,
Section&nbsp;14.10 shall apply to such proprietary information, notwithstanding
the parties&#146; election that Section&nbsp;14.10 shall not otherwise apply to this
Contract.&#148;</TD>

obligations reduced below both BBB-(&#147;triple B, minus&#148;) as rated by Standard
and Poor&#146;s Rating Group (a division of McGraw-Hill, Inc.), or its successor,

sufficient security in the form, amount and for the term reasonably
acceptable to party Y including, but not limited to, a standby irrevocable
letter of credit, a prepayment, or a performance bond or guaranty, subject

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">1.</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD><B>Section&nbsp;2. Definitions</B></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(a) In Section&nbsp;2.4, delete the definition of &#147;Business Day&#148; and replace it
with the following definition:</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;Business Day&#148; shall mean any day except Saturday, Sunday, or a statutory or
banking holiday observed in either party&#146;s jurisdiction for its principal
place of business. A Business Day shall open at 8:00 a.m. and close at 5:00
p.m. local time for the relevant party&#146;s principal place of business. The
relevant party, in each instance unless otherwise specified, shall be the
party to whom the notice, payment or delivery is being sent and by whom the
notice or payment or delivery is to be received.&#148;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">2.</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD><B>Section&nbsp;6. Taxes</B></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(a) In Section&nbsp;6.2, in the first sentence, after the words &#147;goods and
services tax (&#147;GST&#148;)&#148;, add the words &#147;or any combined or harmonized federal
and provincial goods and services tax or sales tax (&#147;HST&#148;), and after the
words &#147;pursuant to the ETA&#148;, add the words &#147;or any provincial sales tax
legislation&#148;.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(b) In Section&nbsp;6.2, in each of the fourth, fifth, sixth and seventh lines,
after the word &#147;GST&#148;, add the words &#147;or HST&#148;.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%" nowrap align="right">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>(c) In the first line of Sections&nbsp;6.3.1, 6.3.2, 6.3.3, in the third line of
Section&nbsp;6.3.3 and in the second line of Section&nbsp;6.4, after the word &#147;GST&#148;,
add the words &#147;or HST&#148;.</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt"><B>END OF SPECIAL PROVISIONS</B>


<DIV align="center">
<TABLE style="font-size: 10pt" cellspacing="0" border="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt"><B>SECOND AMENDED AND RESTATED NATURAL GAS PURCHASE<BR>
AGREEMENT</B>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;THIS SECOND AMENDED AND RESTATED NATURAL GAS PURCHASE AGREEMENT
(&#147;Agreement&#148;), made as of the 1st day of January, 2005.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">BETWEEN:



<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Selkirk Cogen Partners, L.P., a Delaware limited partnership with its principal
place of business in Selkirk, New York (&#147;Buyer&#148;)


<P align="right" style="font-size: 10pt">OF THE FIRST PART



<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">- and &#150;



<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">EnCana Corporation, a Canadian corporation, with its principal place of
business in Calgary, Alberta (&#147;Seller&#148;)


<P align="right" style="font-size: 10pt">OF THE SECOND PART



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;WHEREAS Buyer desires to purchase and receive a long-term, firm natural
gas supply from Seller and Seller desires to sell and deliver a long-term, firm
natural gas supply to Buyer.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;WHEREAS the parties entered into a long term Natural Gas Purchase
Agreement dated August&nbsp;12, 1991, as amended by subsequent letter agreements
(the &#147;Amended August&nbsp;12, 1991 Agreement&#148;);


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;WHEREAS the parties amended and restated the Amended August&nbsp;12, 1991
Agreement by an Amended and Restated Natural Gas Purchase Agreement dated
October&nbsp;22, 1992 (the &#147;1992 Amended Agreement&#148;);


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;AND WHEREAS the parties desire to amend and restate the 1992 Amended
Agreement upon the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, which
shall supersede and replace the 1992 Amended Agreement effective as of January
1, 2005.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and the mutual covenants
herein contained, the parties agree as follows:


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-1-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE I<BR>
<U>INTERPRETATION</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">1.1 <U>Definitions</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The following terms, when used in this Agreement, shall have the following
meanings:


<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(a)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Intentionally Left Blank</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(b)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Intentionally Left Blank</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(c)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;<U>Affiliate</U>&#148; shall have the meaning ascribed to that term in
the <I>Business Corporation Act </I>of Alberta;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(d)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;<U>Base Gas</U>&#148; shall mean all gas under this Agreement;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(e)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;<U>British thermal unit</U>&#148; or &#147;<U>Btu</U>&#148; shall mean the amount
of heat required to raise the temperature of one (1)&nbsp;pound of distilled
water one (1)&nbsp;degree Fahrenheit from sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60&#176;F) to
sixty-one degrees Fahrenheit (61&#176;F) at a constant pressure of fourteen
and seventy-three hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.73
PSIA);</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(f)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;<U>Business Day</U>&#148; shall mean any Day which is not a Saturday,
Sunday or legal or statutory holiday in either Calgary, Alberta or
Selkirk, New York;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">

Transporters;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

    <TD width="4%" nowrap align="right">(h)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>&#147;<U>Buyer&#146;s Plant</U>&#148; shall mean a gas-fired cogeneration power
plant of approximately 260 MW constructed by Buyer in Selkirk, New York;</TD>

    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>

which substantially adopts or duplicates such legislation.

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE V<BR>
<U>COMMENCEMENT AND NOMINATION OF DELIVERIES</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">5.1 Intentionally Left Blank



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">5.2 <U>Nomination</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The parties shall coordinate their nomination activities giving sufficient
time to meet the deadlines of Seller&#146;s Transporter and TCPL (the
&#147;Transporters&#148;). Each party shall give the other party timely prior written
notice, sufficient to meet the requirements of the Transporters of the Daily
Nomination each Day to be delivered at the Delivery


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-10-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">Point. Should either
party become aware that actual deliveries at the Delivery Point are greater or
less than the Daily Nomination for such Day, such party shall promptly notify
the other party. The parties shall use commercially reasonable efforts to
avoid imposition of any Imbalance Charges. &#147;Imbalance Charges&#148; shall mean any
fees, penalties, costs or charges (in cash or in kind) assessed by a
Transporter for failure to satisfy its balance and/or nomination requirements.
If Buyer or Seller receives an invoice from the Transporter that includes
Imbalance Charges, the parties shall determine the validity as well as the
cause of such Imbalance Charges. If the Imbalance Charges are incurred as a
result of Buyer&#146;s receipt of quantities of gas greater than or less than the
Daily Nomination, then Buyer shall pay for such Imbalance Charges or reimburse
Seller for such Imbalance Charges paid by Seller. If the Imbalance Charges are
incurred as a result of Seller&#146;s delivery of quantities of gas greater than or
less than the Daily Nomination, then Seller shall pay for such Imbalance
Charges or reimburse Buyer for such Imbalance Charges paid by Buyer.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE VI<BR>

<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">6.1 <U>Monthly Contract Price</U>

an amount to be comprised of the sum of: (i)&nbsp;a Monthly Charge determined in
accordance with Section&nbsp;6.2; and (ii)&nbsp;a Commodity Charge determined in
accordance with Section&nbsp;6.4.

</DIV>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 2%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">pursuant to Section&nbsp;6.2(a)
multiplied by a fraction, the numerator of which shall be the total quantity
of Base Gas delivered hereunder to TCPL for Buyer&#146;s account during such
Month, and the denominator of which shall be the total of the Daily
Nominations on each Day of the Month. Any failure by Seller to perform its
obligations under the terms of the Agreement when and to the extent such
failure is due to force majeure shall be subject to the provisions of Article
15.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">6.3 <U>Fixed Monthly Charge</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Fixed Monthly Charge (&#147;FMC&#148;) shall, in respect of the particular
Month, be equal to the product of $ (U.S.) 0.30/MMBtu and the sum of the DCQ,
expressed in MMBtu&#146;s in effect for each Day in the particular Month.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">6.4 <U>Commodity Charge</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The &#147;Commodity Charge&#148; for each Month shall be an amount equal to the
product of all volumes of Base Gas nominated and delivered at the Delivery
Point, and the Commodity Rate. The Commodity Rate shall be an amount
determined in accordance with the following formula:


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CR
= ABP - $(U.S.) 0.30/MMBtu


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">Where:



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&#147;CR&#148; is the Commodity Rate in $(U.S.)/MMBtu;



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&#147;ABP&#148; is the Adjusted Base Price for such Month as determined in accordance with Section&nbsp;6.5.



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">6.5 <U>Adjusted Base Price</U>



<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(a)&nbsp;The Adjusted Base Price (&#147;ABP&#148;) is subject to monthly adjustment to reflect
changes in the Regional Weighted Average Price, as defined in Subsection
6.5(c), for certain fuels, if there is a variance between the Regional Weighted
Average Price for the period ending the 21st Day of the most recent preceding
Month for which data is available and beginning on the 22nd Day of the next
preceding Month (&#147;Period&#148;) and the Regional Weighted Average Price for the
twelve (12)&nbsp;Month period ending December&nbsp;31, 1990 (the &#147;Base Period&#148;).


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(b)&nbsp;Buyer will notify Seller of an adjustment on or before the first Day of the
delivery Month during which such adjustment shall be in effect and provide
Seller with the basis for the adjustment; provided however that Seller may
contact Buyer to correct
calculation errors apparent on the face of the adjustment, and Seller may audit
such adjustment pursuant to Section&nbsp;7.3.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(c)&nbsp;The ABP shall be determined monthly and computed in accordance with the
following formula before the last Day of the Month preceding the Month for
which the adjustment is being determined:

<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">Where:



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&#147;ABP&#148; is the Adjusted Base Price;



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&#147;IBP&#148; is U.S. $1.70 per MMBtu;



<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">&#147;RWAP<SUB>1</SUB>&#148; is the Regional Weighted Average Price expressed in $U.S./MMBtu for the
most recent Period preceding the Month for which the adjustment is being
determined; and


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">&#147;RWAP<SUB>B</SUB>&#148; is the Regional Weighted Average Price for the Base Period of U.S.
$3.7062 per MMBtu.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(d)&nbsp;For the purpose of this Section&nbsp;6.5, No.&nbsp;2 fuel oil, No.&nbsp;6 fuel oil, and
natural gas shall be the &#147;Regional Fuels&#148;. The weightings of each Regional
Fuel in any contract year shall be 26% for No.&nbsp;2 fuel oil, 9% for No.&nbsp;6 fuel
oil and 65% for natural gas (&#147;Regional Fuel Weights&#148;).


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(e)&nbsp;The price for each of the fuel oil Regional Fuels for any Period will be
multiplied by the applicable Regional Fuel Weight for such fuel oil Regional
Fuel and the sum of such calculations will be the weighted average wholesale
price of the fuel oil Regional Fuels for the Region for such Period (&#147;Regional
Weighted Average Fuel Oil Price&#148;).


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(f)&nbsp;The Regional Gas Price expressed in $U.S./MMBtu for each Period will be the
arithmetic average of the FERC CD-5 rate of Tennessee Gas Pipeline Company, the
FERC DCQ-D rate of Texas Eastern Gas Transmission Corp. and the firm service
rate of Transcontinental Gas Pipe Line Corp. for New York City citygate
deliveries, (in the manner calculated in Appendix &#147;B&#148; to this Agreement) each
as in effect as of the last Day of such Period (without regard to any
subsequent changes in the effective rate for such Day), all at 100% load
factor. For any Period, the product of the Regional Gas Price and the
applicable Regional Fuel Weight for gas for such Period will be the Regional
Weighted Average Gas Price.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(g)&nbsp;For each Period, the sum of the Regional Weighted Average Fuel Oil Price
and Regional Weighted Average Gas Price will be the Regional Weighted Average
Price for such Period.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(h)&nbsp;The prices in each Period for the fuel oil Regional Fuels will be the
average of the high and the low of the daily prices (in U.S. dollars per MMBtu)
for such Period for
such fuel oil Regional Fuels as reported in &#147;Platt&#146;s Oilgram Price Report&#148;
published by McGraw-Hill, Inc. for (i)&nbsp;the No.&nbsp;2 fuel oil Regional Fuel for
&#147;MetroNY (Eth) Diesel No.&nbsp;2 Fuel&#148;, and if the MetroNY (Eth) price is not
published for any Period, the reference price will be &#147;N. New Jersey (Eth), and
(ii)&nbsp;the No.&nbsp;6 fuel oil Regional Fuel for &#147;New York/Boston; $/Bb/; No.&nbsp;6 1%S
Max; Barge&#148; under the heading &#147;Product Price Assessments.&#148;


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-13-
</DIV>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">




<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(i)&nbsp;In the event that any of the published data referenced in this Article&nbsp;VI
is no longer available, the parties shall use their best efforts to agree on
substitute data or a substitute index. If the parties are unable to agree upon
substitute data or substitute index, the Commodity Escalation Factor shall be
determined in the same manner that the escalation factor for Consolidated
Edison Company of New York Inc.&#146;s purchases of gas from Boundary Gas, Inc. is
then determined. If the parties cannot agree on substitute data or substitute
index, and, Boundary Gas, Inc. has no subsisting long-term gas purchase
contract with Consolidated Edison Company of New York Inc., then at such time
the provisions of Section&nbsp;6.8 shall apply.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">6.6 <U>Minimum Bill</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon the Commencement of Firm Deliveries, the minimum monthly bill shall
be the Monthly Charge.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.7 Intentionally Left Blank


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">6.8 <U>Replacement Indices</U>


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(a)&nbsp;If the parties cannot agree on substitute data or a substitute index
pursuant to Section&nbsp;6.5(i) and if Boundary Gas, Inc. has no subsisting
long-term gas purchase contract with Consolidated Edison Company of New York
Inc., then the procedures set forth in Section&nbsp;6.8(b) below shall apply
<U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, to the extent the results of such proceedings
under Section&nbsp;6.8(b) require regulatory approval, which may include short term
approvals, then the effectiveness of the alternate Reference Price calculated
in accordance with Section&nbsp;6.8(b) shall be subject to the receipt of all
governmental and regulatory approvals required to make the Reference Price
effective without modifications (unless such modifications are acceptable to
both parties); the parties shall promptly apply for such approvals if required.
The purpose of any such proceeding with respect to the substitute data or
substitute index shall be to determine substitute data or a substitute index
that is comparable in all material respects to the formerly published data or
index for which a substitute is required.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">(b) , If the publication reporting the price based upon a published index (the
&#147;Reference Price&#148;) prior to its unavailability has suggested an alternate index
or methodology for determining the Reference Price, then the alternate
Reference Price shall be that
suggested by such publication. If none is suggested, then the parties agree to
promptly and in good faith negotiate an alternate Reference Price.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">If the parties do not agree on a substitute methodology or index by the end of
the first Month for which the Reference Price could not be determined, then
each party shall in good faith prepare a list of three (3)&nbsp;differing alternate
published reference postings or prices representative of spot prices for gas
delivered in the same geographic area as


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-14-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">




<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Base Gas delivered hereunder. Each
list shall be set forth in that party&#146;s priority order with the highest
priority index listed first.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">Each party shall submit its list to the other within ten (10)&nbsp;Business Days
after the end of the first Month for which the price could not be determined as
set forth above. The first listed index appearing in Seller&#146;s list that also
appears in Buyer&#146;s list shall constitute the alternate Reference Price. If
either party fails to provide a list of that party&#146;s alternate published
references as provided above, such party&#146;s list shall not be considered, and
the first listed index appearing in the other party&#146;s submitted list shall
constitute the alternate Reference Price.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">If there is no index common to both Seller&#146;s and Buyer&#146;s list then the parties
shall continue to attempt to reach agreement on an index for an additional five
(5)&nbsp;Day period. If no selection can be agreed upon within the specified
timeframe, then the average of each party&#146;s first listed index in its first
submitted list shall constitute the alternate Reference Price.


<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">From and after the date the indices used to determine the Reference Price are
no longer available (&#147;Renegotiation Date&#148;), until the alternate Reference Price
is determined, the Reference Price shall be deemed to be the average of the
Reference Price(s) in effect during the twelve (12)&nbsp;Months preceding the Month
in which the Renegotiation Date occurred, which price shall be effective until
the effective date of the alternate Reference Price determined as set forth
above. Upon determination of a new alternate Reference Price, the Reference
Price will be adjusted retroactively to the Renegotiation Date

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE VII<BR>
<U>BILLINGS AND PAYMENTS</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">7.1 <U>Monthly Statements and Payments</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Subject to Seller&#146;s receipt of TCPL&#146;s metering statements pursuant to
Section&nbsp;8.1 hereof, Seller shall prepare and send to Buyer on or before the
thirteenth (13)&nbsp;Day of each month after the first sale of gas hereunder a
statement for the preceding month in which the gas being billed for was sold
(the &#147;Sale Month&#148;) showing the daily and total quantity of gas sold hereunder,
the applicable Price and the total amount payable to Seller therefore stated in
United States dollars (the &#147;Sum&#148;) with any amounts billed Seller in Canadian
dollars converted to $ U.S./ MMBtu pursuant to Section&nbsp;21.2. Buyer


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-15-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">shall pay
all amounts due on or before the 25th Day of the Month following the Month of
delivery by direct deposit to the Royal Bank of Canada, 339 &#150;
8<SUP>th</SUP> Avenue S.W.,
Calgary, Alberta, T2P 1C9, Swift Address: ROYCATT2, Beneficiary US$ Acct. No.:
400-484-2, Duns No.&nbsp;25-537-8655; Intermediary Information: Chase Manhattan
Bank, New York, ABA No.: 021000021, or such other bank account as Seller may
direct by notice given to Buyer pursuant to Article&nbsp;XIX. In the event that
Seller fails to so provide a statement to Buyer on or before the thirteenth
(13th) Day of a Month, the date by which Buyer must deposit the Sum in Seller&#146;s
account shall be extended one Day for each Day Seller&#146;s statement is late;
<U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, that if Seller is unable to render a statement
on or before the thirteenth (13th) Day of a Month, Seller may at its option
provide an estimated statement to Buyer which statement shall contain Seller&#146;s
best estimate of the daily and total quantity of gas sold hereunder during the
preceding month, and the total amount payable by Buyer therefore stated in
United States dollars. Buyer shall deposit in Seller&#146;s account the Sum for
such estimated statement within fifteen (15)&nbsp;Days of its receipt but no later
than the 28th Day of the Month. For any Month in which Seller provides an
estimated statement to Buyer, Seller shall provide the final statement for such
Month with Seller&#146;s statement for the next succeeding Month. Seller&#146;s
statement for such next succeeding Month shall reflect an adjustment for any
difference between the estimated statement and the final statement for the
previous Month, which shall be added to or deducted from, as appropriate,
Seller&#146;s statement for such next succeeding month. If Buyer fails to deposit
the Sum or any portion thereof, in Seller&#146;s account when same is due, interest
thereon shall accrue both before and after judgment at the rate of interest
which is equal to the Prime Rate during the period of time such payment remains
outstanding, plus two hundred (200)&nbsp;basis points until the same is paid.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">7.2 <U>Failure to Pay</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If Buyer&#146;s failure to pay continues for fifteen (15)&nbsp;Days after payment is
due, Seller, in addition to all other remedies, may thereafter suspend the sale
of gas hereunder and if such default continues for forty-five (45)&nbsp;additional
Days, Seller may thereafter, in addition to any other rights Seller may have,
terminate this Contract; <U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, in order for Seller
to have the right to suspend sales or terminate this Agreement, Seller must
first have notified Buyer in writing fifteen (15)&nbsp;Days prior to exercising such
right of its intent to do so and give Buyer the right to pay the amount so due
to Seller within such fifteen (15)&nbsp;Day period; and provided further that if
Buyer in good faith shall dispute the amount of any such bill or any part
thereof and shall pay to Seller such amounts as it concedes to be correct and
at any time thereafter within twenty (20)&nbsp;Days of a demand made by Seller shall
furnish or cause to be furnished a good and sufficient surety bond acceptable
to Seller acting reasonably, guaranteeing


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-16-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">payment to Seller of the amount
ultimately found due upon such bill after a final determination which may be
reached either by agreement or judgment of the courts, as may be the case, then
Seller shall not be entitled to suspend further sales of gas or terminate this
Agreement because of such non-payment. Interest on the final determination
amount shall accrue to the successful party in the dispute both before and
after judgment at the Prime Rate plus two hundred (200)&nbsp;basis points until the
same is paid from the date of dispute to the date of payment.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">7.3 <U>Audits</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon prior written notice, either party hereto shall have the right at all
times during normal business hours to audit those accounts, books, records and
charts of the other party which are necessary to verify the accuracy of any
statement, charge, computation or demand made under or pursuant to this
Agreement or related transportation agreements. Any error, audit exceptions or
discrepancy in charts or statements furnished pursuant hereto shall be promptly
reported to Seller or Buyer, as applicable, and proper adjustment thereof shall
be made within thirty (30)&nbsp;Days after final determination of the correct
volumes or amounts involved. If either party fails to make payment when due,
interest thereon shall accrue both before and after judgment at the rate of
interest which is equal to the Prime Rate plus two hundred (200)&nbsp;basis points
until the same is paid during the period of time such payment remains
outstanding.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">7.4 <U>Currency</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All statements and payments hereunder shall be expressed and made in U.S.
dollars and all Canadian dollar amounts shall be converted to $ U.S./MMBtu
pursuant to Section&nbsp;21.2.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">7.5 <U>Indemnity Payments</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seller shall pay to Buyer any amounts which Seller has agreed to indemnify
Buyer against under this Agreement within thirty (30)&nbsp;Days of Buyer rendering
an invoice. Unpaid amounts shall accrue interest both before and after
judgment at a rate and in the manner described in Section&nbsp;7.1 and Buyer may
offset any amounts owing to it against amounts otherwise payable by it to
Seller. This Section&nbsp;7.5 shall not apply to Indemnity Amounts subject to the
provisions of Section&nbsp;20.2.

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE VIII<BR>
<U>DELIVERY POINT</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">8.1 <U>Delivery Point</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Delivery of gas by Seller to Buyer shall be at the Delivery Point. It is
understood that Buyer&#146;s request for the Daily Nomination shall be made by TCPL
for Buyer&#146;s account and that gas sold hereunder by Seller shall be delivered by
Seller&#146;s Transporter to TCPL for Buyer&#146;s account and not for TCPL&#146;s own
account. Volumes delivered at the Delivery Point for Buyer&#146;s account shall be
determined by the meters of TCPL at the Delivery Point. Buyer shall forward to
Seller copies of TCPL&#146;s metering statements within three (3)&nbsp;Business Days of
Buyer&#146;s receipt thereof.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">8.2 <U>Title</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Title to gas delivered hereunder shall pass to Buyer when it is received
on behalf of Buyer at the Delivery Point. All risks, costs and expenses of
delivering the gas to the Delivery Point shall be borne by Seller except to the
extent herein otherwise specifically provided. Similarly, all risks, costs and
expenses of transporting the gas beyond the Delivery Point shall be borne by
Buyer except to the extent herein otherwise specifically provided.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">8.3 <U>Possession</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As between the parties hereto, Seller shall be, or shall be deemed to be,
in exclusive control and possession of the gas sold hereunder and responsible
for any loss, damage or injury caused thereby until such gas is delivered at
the Delivery Point, at which time Buyer shall be deemed to be in exclusive
control and possession of such gas
and responsible for any loss, damage or injury caused thereby. Seller
shall indemnify and save Buyer harmless from all suits, claims, liens, damages,
costs, losses, expenses and encumbrances of whatsoever nature arising from and
out of claims of any or all persons to said gas or title thereto, or to
royalties, taxes, license fees, TOPGAS charges, payments or other charges
thereon applicable before title passes to Buyer, and Buyer shall indemnify and
save Seller harmless from all suits, claims, liens, damages, costs, losses,
expenses and encumbrances of whatsoever nature arising from and out of claims
of any or all persons to said gas or title thereto, or to royalties, taxes,
license fees, payments or other charges thereon applicable after title passes
to Buyer.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">8.4 <U>Change of Delivery Point</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At any time and from time to time at the request of either party the
parties shall meet to discuss a possible change of delivery point in respect of
all or a portion of


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-18-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">the gas to be delivered hereunder, and upon the mutual
agreement of the parties in writing, the Delivery Point shall be as so agreed
upon.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE IX<BR>
<U> </U> <U>DELIVERY PRESSURE</U>



<P align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; text-indent: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 10pt">9.1 Gas delivered by or on behalf of Seller to or for the account of Buyer
hereunder shall be at the pressure required from time to time to enter the
facilities of the transporter receiving the gas at the Delivery Point.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE X<BR>
<U> </U> <U>QUALITY</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">10.1 <U>Specifications</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The gas delivered by Seller shall be of a quality and pressure sufficient
to be acceptable to and enter the facilities of the transporter receiving the
gas at the Delivery Point.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">10.2 <U>Off Specification</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the gas offered for delivery by Seller hereunder shall fail at any time
to conform to the quality requirements of the transporter receiving gas at the
Delivery Point, then Buyer shall notify Seller of such failure and, at Buyer&#146;s
option, may refuse to purchase such gas pending correction by Seller in which
case Seller shall be deemed to have failed to deliver such gas.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE XI<BR>
<U>MEASUREMENT</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">11.1 <U>Units</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The unit of measurement of gas for purposes of billing shall be MMBtu&#146;s<B><I>.</I></B>


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">11.2 <U>Quantity Determined by Transporter</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The quantity of gas delivered to transporter for Buyer&#146;s account at the
Delivery Point shall be determined by transporter receiving gas at the Delivery
Point in accordance with the then current standard terms and conditions
applicable to such transporter&#146;s transportation service.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-19-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">

<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">11.3 <U>Conversions</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Where required, standards of measurement shall be converted to imperial
measurement in accordance with the provisions of Article&nbsp;XXI.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE XII<BR>
<U>REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">12.1 <U>Seller&#146;s Representations and Warranties</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seller represents and warrants to Buyer that:


<P>

    <TD width="2%" nowrap align="right">(a)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Seller has good title and the right to sell to Buyer the gas
delivered hereunder;</TD>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD width="2%" nowrap align="right">(b)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>all such gas shall be free from any and all liens, encumbrances and
adverse claims of any nature;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="2%" nowrap align="right">(c)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>no finding of producer support pursuant to the Natural Gas Marketing
Act (Alberta) or similar legislation of any Canadian jurisdiction is
required and no approval by a joint owner of gas reserves is required in
order for Seller to sell and deliver gas to Buyer hereunder;</TD>

<TR>

Agreement have been duly authorized by all necessary corporate action on

<TR>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE XIII<BR>
<U>TAXES</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">13.1 <U>Responsibility for Taxes</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Subject to Section&nbsp;13.2, Seller shall pay or cause to be paid all taxes,
royalties and other assessments and levies imposed on Seller with respect to
the gas delivered hereunder prior to or on a concurrent basis with its delivery
to Buyer including, but without limitation, all severance and sales taxes and
Buyer shall pay or cause to be paid all taxes and assessments imposed upon
Buyer with respect to gas delivered hereunder after its receipt by Buyer.
Neither party shall be responsible or liable for any taxes or other statutory
charges levied or assessed against any of the facilities of the other party
used for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Agreement.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">13.2 <U>GST</U>



<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%" nowrap align="right">(a)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>The parties intend that the Price does not include any amounts
payable under GST. The parties further intend that the transactions
contemplated in this Agreement relate solely to exports from Canada and
accordingly shall be zero rated for GST purposes and not subject to GST.
Each party agrees to provide to the other party, or to such third party
as may be directed by the other party, any declarations, certificates,
and documents evidencing transactions pursuant to this Agreement as may
be requested hereunder or may be required by law.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%" nowrap align="right">(b)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Notwithstanding Subsection 13.2(a), if the GST is imposed by law upon
Buyer in respect of its purchase of gas from Seller, or the
transportation of such gas in Canada, or the export of such gas from
Canada, and such law or regulations thereunder permit the refund of such
GST amounts paid to Buyer then Buyer shall pay such GST and Seller shall
use reasonable efforts to assist Buyer in recovering any such tax or
levy including assisting Buyer in applying for a refund of such amounts
provided that Buyer shall conduct and bear the costs of any application
for a refund.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%" nowrap align="right">(c)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>In the event that GST is imposed on gas sold hereunder and to the
extent that such GST is paid by Buyer and not refunded, such GST amounts
paid, and not refunded, shall be reimbursed to Buyer by Seller each
Month to the extent only
that gas sold under this Agreement in the applicable Month has a
delivered price at Buyer&#146;s Plant in excess of the &#147;Ceiling Price&#148; (as
such term is defined in paragraph II.D of Appendix&nbsp;C in Buyer&#146;s Power
Purchase Contract) for the applicable Month, <U>provided</U>
<U>however</U> that Seller shall not be required to reimburse Buyer for
GST amounts paid by Buyer in respect of gas which Buyer has not exported
from Canada.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="3%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="1%" nowrap align="right">(d)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>From time to time, Buyer shall provide the Seller with evidence of
export of the natural gas purchased under this Agreement acceptable to
the Seller.</TD>
</TR>

<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seller shall beneficially own and produce sufficient gas reserves and

<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seller acknowledges that this Article is included in order to provide
additional assurances to Buyer that gas will be provided by Seller to Buyer in
accordance with this Agreement and is not intended to limit the liability of
Seller to Buyer for damages or
under any indemnity arising from any failure by Seller to perform its
obligations under this Agreement.


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">ARTICLE XV<BR>
<U>FORCE MAJEURE</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">15.1 <U>Definition</U>



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Seller shall not be liable for any failure to perform the terms of this
Agreement when and to the extent such failure is due to &#147;force majeure&#148; and,
notwithstanding Section&nbsp;6.2, Buyer shall not be obligated to make any payments
under this Agreement in


<P align="center" style="font-size: 10pt">-24-
</DIV>

<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif">



<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">respect of any Monthly Charge, or the relevant portion
thereof, when Buyer has been unable to nominate or take at the Delivery Point
or transport to or consume gas and sell electricity from Buyer&#146;s Plant due to
an event of force majeure. The term &#147;force majeure&#148;, as employed, herein and
for all purposes relating hereto, shall mean acts of God; strikes; lockouts or
other industrial disturbances; acts of public enemy; wars; blockades;
insurrections; riots; epidemics; landslides; lightning; earthquakes;
explosions; fires; civil disturbance; mechanical breakdowns; a failure of
Seller&#146;s gas gathering or processing facilities for reasons clearly beyond the
control of Seller which materially impairs Seller&#146;s ability to deliver gas to
its long term customers; intervention of federal, provincial, state or local
government or from any of their agencies or boards including Buyer&#146;s Regulatory
Authorities and Seller&#146;s Regulatory Authorities; the order or direction of any
court; or accidents affecting Buyer&#146;s Plant or Buyer&#146;s Transporters or Seller&#146;s
Transporters used to transport gas to the Delivery Point or Buyer&#146;s
Transporters&#146; facilities used to transport gas from the Delivery Point to the
Buyer&#146;s Plant; force majeure events under Buyer&#146;s Power Purchase Agreement; and
any other causes whether of the kind herein enumerated or otherwise, not within
the control of the party claiming suspension and which by the exercise of due
diligence such party is unable to prevent or overcome.


<P align="left" style="font-size: 10pt">15.2 <U>Exclusions</U>



<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>Notwithstanding Section&nbsp;15.1, the following shall not be events of force
majeure:</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>


<P>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 10pt">

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 10pt; color: #000000; background: transparent">
    <TD width="6%" nowrap align="right">(i)</TD>
    <TD width="1%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>insufficiency of Seller&#146;s gas supplies or
deliverability to the NOVA system;</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
    <TD colspan="5">&nbsp;</TD>

to the payment of any amount or amounts then due hereunder; and</TD>
